24/11/2009
PRAGUE, Czech Republic -- The head of the Czech contingent in Kosovo, Jiri Kyvala, has been suspended for an undisclosed period after incidents involving Czech soldiers, the interior ministry in Prague announced on Monday (November 23rd). 
The statement came after a Czech soldier was reportedly shot and wounded on Saturday. 
A special commission from the Czech Republic will visit Kosovo to investigate the incident. 
(Radio Free Europe, Blic, Telegrafi - 23/11/09)
